pull_request.title: Add status subresource to StorageProfile
pull_request.body:
We have been observing flaky failures in the StorageProfile functional tests.

The root cause appears to be a race condition. Each test resets the spec upon completion, but the controller is likely still processing the previous state when the next test begins. Without a status field, the test has no way to confirm that the controller has finished reconciling the previous state.

This change introduces a status subresource to the StorageProfile. This allows tests and clients to observe the resource's actual state and wait for the status field to be populated - signaling that reconciliation is complete before proceeding.

The implementation includes:

1. Adding the +kubebuilder:subresource:status annotation to the StorageProfile type.
2. Updating the controller to handle status updates separately from the spec.
3. Regenerating the CRD to support the status subresource.

pull_request.title: Add status subresource to StorageProfile
pull_request.body:
We have been observing flaky failures in the StorageProfile functional tests.

The root cause appears to be a race condition. Each test resets the spec upon completion, but the controller is likely still processing the previous state when the next test begins. Without a status field, the test has no way to confirm that the controller has finished reconciling the previous state.

This change introduces a status subresource to the StorageProfile. This allows tests and clients to observe the resource's actual state and wait for the status field to be populated - signaling that reconciliation is complete before proceeding.

The implementation includes:

1. Adding the +kubebuilder:subresource:status annotation to the StorageProfile type.
2. Updating the controller to handle status updates separately from the spec.
3. Regenerating the CRD to support the status subresource.

issue.title: Pasting in a JSON payload with newlines inside the produce screen causes the record to get prematurely produced
issue.body:
Repro steps:

1. Copy some JSON payload with newlines in it. 
2. Get to the produce screen for a topic, navigate to the payload section
3. Paste the text into the payload input. 

Expected:
The JSON for the payload should get pasted in. 

Actual:
The newlines in the JSON look like they're triggering the form to advance, so the first newline will select the "Produce" button, then the next will trigger a produce. 

Note: JSON with no newlines in it is pasted in ok, so seems the newlines are the cause.

issue.title: Any way to make r3dfox compatible with or able to run legacy DownThemAll! v3.0.8 extension/add-on?
issue.body:
Just a random n00bie question. I currently have Firefox v52 ESR installed for the one and only purpose of being able to run the best download manager there has ever been for Firefox, being dTa! v3.0.8. I don't know the full backstory, only enough to know that FF v52 ESR was the last conventional version that allowed dTa! to run in its old version that worked the best.

Having only recently discovered r3dfox, I was wondering if it were possible to customise it to be able to install the dTa! 3.0.8 xpi and therefore allow me to finally retire FF v52 and reduce the number of browsers my computer has installed? I suspect the dTa! v3 standalone installer xpi file is not easy to find anymore since it's now something like 7 years old (last updated 3 June 2018). I can provide the xpi file if need be.

For reference, dTa v3 was able to integrate itself into the browser/windows download dialog box such that clicking a link would directly connect you to a dialog that would call dTa to take over the download. After v3 this functionality was gone and it became much more cumbersome to use.

issue.title: Implement Clean Architecture
issue.body:
<open-swe-issue-content>Structure the code according to "clean architecture". Use best practices, principles, patterns. It should be easy to extend the code.</open-swe-issue-content>
<details>
<summary>Agent Context</summary>
<open-swe-do-not-edit-proposed-plan>
[
  "Create a new directory structure within the `backend/project` directory to align with Clean Architecture principles. This will involve creating `domain`, `application`, `infrastructure` and `api` directories. The `api` directory will be the new home for the Flask blueprints and routes. The existing `api` directory will be renamed to `api_old` to avoid conflicts.\n",
  "Move the existing SQLAlchemy models from `backend/project/models` to the new `backend/project/domain/models` directory. These models represent the core domain entities of the application.\n",
  "Create a new `backend/project/domain/repositories` directory and define abstract repository interfaces for each domain entity. For example, create a `user_repository.py` with an abstract `UserRepository` class that defines methods for interacting with user data.\n",
  "Move the business logic from the existing services and tasks into the `backend/project/application/services` directory. Each service will encapsulate a specific use case and will depend on the domain repositories to interact with the data. For example, create a `workflow_service.py` that handles the logic for creating, updating, and executing workflows.\n",
  "Implement the repository interfaces defined in the domain layer within the `backend/project/infrastructure/repositories` directory. These implementations will be specific to SQLAlchemy and will handle the actual database operations. For example, create a `sqlalchemy_user_repository.py` that implements the `UserRepository` interface.\n",
  "Refactor the existing API routes in `backend/project/api_old/routes` to use the application services. The routes will be moved to the new `backend/project/api/routes` directory and will be responsible for handling HTTP requests and responses, but will delegate the business logic to the application services.\n",
  "Update the Flask application factory in `backend/project/__init__.py` to register the new API blueprints and to inject the dependencies (e.g., repositories) into the application services. This will be done using a dependency injection container or a simple factory function.\n",
  "Finally, remove the old `api_old`, `models`, `services`, and `tasks` directories to complete the refactoring.\n"
]
</open-swe-do-not-edit-proposed-plan>
</details>
